HEADWORD: Autophony
<hw>Au*toph"o*ny</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Auto-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a sound.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An auscultatory process, which consists in noting the tone of the
observer's own voice, while he speaks, holding his head close to the
patient's chest.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

